Usage:
  zscalerctl [flags]
  zscalerctl [command]

Available Commands:
  auth        inspect authentication configuration
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  config      manage zscalerctl configuration
  diff        compare two dump directories and report configuration drift
  doctor      check configuration, credentials, and connectivity
  dump        write a full or filtered resource dump to a directory
  help        Help about any command
  introspect  print a machine-readable map of all commands, flags, and resources (JSON)
  schema      inspect the resource catalog schema
  version     print version, commit, build date, and runtime info
  zcc         read zcc resources
  zia         read zia resources
  zidentity   read zidentity resources
  zpa         read zpa resources
  ztw         read ztw resources

Flags:
      --color string         color output: auto, always, never (default "auto")
      --config string        config file path
      --fields string        comma-separated output fields to keep (narrows the sanitized output)
      --filter stringArray   narrow list results: key=value (exact) or key~value (substring); repeatable, all must match
      --format string        output format: auto, table, json, ndjson, pretty (default "auto")
  -h, --help                 help for zscalerctl
      --log-level string     diagnostic logging to stderr: off, error, warn, info, debug (default "off")
      --no-cache             bypass API cache where supported
      --no-color             disable color output
      --output string        output path
      --profile string       profile name
      --redaction string     redaction mode: standard, share, paranoid
      --search string        narrow list results to records whose rendered values contain term (case-insensitive)
      --timeout duration     request timeout (default 30s)

Use "zscalerctl [command] --help" for more information about a command.
